comment.narrative:
1. Center for Continuous Electoral Training is capable to use the E-Learning Platform; at least 3,000 electoral officials certified through online trainings;
2. Amendments to Electoral Code developed; Law no. 101 revised/or a new one developed; SAISE Concept paper updated;
3. CEC is fully capable to monitor and manage the political parties financing 
4. Regulatory framework of the address system developed. IT system of the address register modernized. The interoperability with the State Register of Voters of at least 2 key-state registers fully established.

1. 4 training modules of CCET for  2015 local elections gender mainstreamed;
2. At least 40% women in senior management positions of District Electoral Commissions; 50% women in senior leadership positions in Precinct Electoral Commissions 
3.At least  2 voter education campaigns targeting specific groups of voters (women from vulnerable groups, Roma, other ethnic minority women) conducted prior to 2015 local elections in support to CEC voter education and awareness campaign;
4. At least 4 regional parliamentary forums bringing constituents from vulnerable groups, particularly women, and MPs facilitated;  
5. Capacities of all 11 newly elected women MPs enhanced through training in the areas of strategic political communications, media skills and public image
6.  Up to  100 women councilors (local and district) from 5 pilot districts enhances capacities in areas of legislation, roles  and responsibilities of councilors, finance and fundraising, gender   and communications
